# Install dependencies

1. Run the R-programming language from a bash terminal by executing the command R

2. Run the following R commands

install.packages('parallel')
install.packages('data.table')
install.packages('zoo')
install.packages('scales')

3. Verify all dependencies are properly installed by running the following R-commands

library(data.table)
library(zoo)
library(scales)
library(parallel)

4. Give execution permissions to the bash script by running the following bash command:

chmod 777 binomL.sh

5. Test binomL.sh by running:
./binomL.sh --help

6. Run the example:

./binomL.sh -t absolute_path_to_target_file -i absolute_path_to_single_fragment.epiread -l 200 -s fwd -N 1000 -R 4 -p 1 -o output_dir -c 1

An example target_file is given: 
regions.txt # Absolute path to this file is required!

An example absolute_path_to_single_fragment.epiread is available at cronus010: 
/media/disk3/bronte/ena_pooled_data/single_epiread_12/single_fragment.epiread
